Philippines Stocks: Ayala Land, First Philippine, Lepanto

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-08-10T04:29:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/ayala-land-first-philippine-globe-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index climbed 3.2 percent to
4,290.14, gaining for the first time in four days. Today’s rally
was the steepest since Dec. 2.  Miners:  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s biggest
metals producer, jumped 8.4 percent to 27.10 pesos, the sharpest
gain since since June 24, after the price of copper rebounded.
 Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LC)  Co.’s Class A shares (LC PM),
reserved for Filipinos, advanced 6.7 percent to 1.28 pesos,
halting a three-day drop.  Copper for three-month delivery rallied for the first time
in six days, with futures rising as much as 3.1 percent to
$9,005 per metric ton on the London Metal Exchange.  Ayala Land Inc. (ALI)  , the  Philippines ’ largest builder,
advanced 4.7 percent to 15.70 pesos, the sharpest jump since
Jan. 27. The builder said first-half profit rose 35 percent to
3.38 billion pesos ($80 million) as home sales and rental
earnings increased. Revenue in the January to June period
increased 15 percent to 21.25 billion pesos, it said.  First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)   increased 1.4
percent to 57.80 pesos, the steepest gain since July 4. The
company bought back 300,000 shares in the open market, a stock
exchange filing showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
